The state should announce the death toll and number of casualties of the Kulbiyow attack in Somalia, as citizens have a right to know, a former legislator has said.&ldquo;Kenyans want to know the exact number of soldiers killed so we can mourn with their families,&rdquo; former Mwala MP Daniel Muoki said yesterday.On Friday, al Shabaab attacked a KDF base in Somalia. They said they killed 57 Kenyan soldiers, a claim KDF denied.